  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The classical Gelfand–Tsetlin formulas provide a basis in terms of tableaux and an explicit action of the generators of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mi mathvariant="fraktur">gl</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> for every irreducible finite-dimensional <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mi mathvariant="fraktur">gl</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> -module. These formulas can be used to define a <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mi mathvariant="fraktur">gl</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> -module structure on some infinite-dimensional modules – the so-called generic Gelfand–Tsetlin modules. The generic Gelfand–Tsetlin modules are convenient to work with since for every generic tableau there exists a unique irreducible generic Gelfand–Tsetlin module containing this tableau as a basis element. In this paper we initiate the systematic study of a large class of non-generic Gelfand–Tsetlin modules – the class of 1-singular Gelfand–Tsetlin modules. An explicit tableaux realization and the action of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mi mathvariant="fraktur">gl</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> on these modules is provided using a new construction which we call derivative tableaux. Our construction of 1-singular modules provides a large family of new irreducible Gelfand–Tsetlin modules of <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><mi mathvariant="fraktur">gl</mi></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>n</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></math> , and is a part of the classification of all such irreducible modules for <math altimg="si3.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>3</mn></math> .</subfield>
